import React from 'react'
import {Container} from 'react-bootstrap'
import {Row} from 'react-bootstrap'
import {Col} from 'react-bootstrap'

function Dashboard() {
    return (

        
        <Container>
     
     <Row>
    <Col>1 of 1</Col>
  </Row>
        {/* Stack the columns on mobile by making one full-width and the other half-width */}
        <Row>
            <Col xs={12} md={8}>
            xs=12 md=8
            </Col>
            <Col xs={6} md={4}>
            xs=6 md=4
            </Col>
        </Row>

        {/* Columns start at 50% wide on mobile and bump up to 33.3% wide on desktop */}
        <Row>
            <Col xs={6} md={4}>
            xs=6 md=4
            </Col>
            <Col xs={6} md={4}>
            xs=6 md=4
            </Col>
            <Col xs={6} md={4}>
            xs=6 md=4
            </Col>
        </Row>

        {/* Columns are always 50% wide, on mobile and desktop */}
        <Row>
            <Col> 
            <canvas class="my-4 w-100 chartjs-render-monitor" id="myChart" width="485" height="203" style="display: block; height: 163px; width: 388px;"></canvas>
            </Col>
            <Col xs={6}>xs=6</Col>
        </Row>
        </Container>
    )
}

export default Dashboard
